export_info.purpose: PCA export for LLM interpretation of Town Meeting voting patterns.

assumptions: Vote encoding is YES=+1, NO=-1, ABSTAIN=0.
If "ignore abstain" is enabled, abstain is treated as missing before imputation.
If "ignore motions to terminate debate" is enabled, those vote columns are removed.
Missing values are imputed per selected strategy: neutral or vote-column mean.
Members with sessions attended below minimum are excluded.
Principal components are computed for top 5 components; residual captures remaining variance magnitude.

instructions.readme_text: This file exports PCA results for Town Meeting voting data. First review parameters and assumptions, then variance_explained, then vote coefficients and member scores. Votes with larger absolute coefficients are more influential for a component; members with larger absolute scores are more strongly aligned to that component.
how_to_read: Use variance_explained to assess component importance.
Use votes[].coefficients to understand which motions load strongly onto each component.
Use members[].scores to locate members on each component axis (positive vs negative direction).
PC signs are relative and can flip; interpret relative magnitude and group separation.
Residual score summarizes unexplained member variation after PC1-PC5.
analyst_notes: Large absolute vote coefficient means that vote is influential for that component.
Large absolute member score means that member is strongly associated with that component.
Compare member score distributions by precinct or session participation when interpreting clusters.

summary.parameter_summary_line: Parameters -> min sessions: 4 | abstain: ignored | term-debate: ignored | missing votes: column mean

votes.title: Article 19 Main Motion to Table
votes.description: Procedural vote: Motion to table (avoid a vote on) Article 19, the resolution regarding the use of the 25th Amendment to remove Donald Trump from office. This motion failed by approximately 10 votes, allowing debate and a vote on the main motion to proceed. Some members left the auditorium in an attempt to prevent a quorum. Submitted by Margolis (TMM7), Smith (TMM6), Weintraub (TMM9), Bassett (TMM6), and Vanderkay (TMM9).

votes.title: Article 19 Main Motion
votes.description: Resolution regarding the use of the 25th Amendment to remove Donald Trump from office. Submitted by Margolis (TMM7) et al. Expresses concern over Trump's fitness for office, citing "numerous actions that demonstrate his unsoundness of mind" and "increasingly frequent and serious violations of the Constitution." Calls for invocation of the 25th Amendment while acknowledging impeachment and the 25th Amendment are "to all intents and purposes unavailable" due to political reality. Passed 141-27-20 in a rare anonymous "counted vote" after members expressed fears of retaliation.
